com.ethercis.servicemanager.service

Class ServiceHolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ethercis.servicemanager.service.ServiceHolder

  • public class ServiceHolder
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the information on how to configure a certain service and when a certain service is invoked by the run level manager 
    
  <service id='storage:CACHE' className='com.privantis.cache.PersistenceCacheService'>
     <attribute id='transientQueue'>storage:RAM</attribute>
     <attribute id='persistentQueue'>storage:JDBC</attribute>
  </service>

        serviceConfig - the object to add to the holder.

      • getServiceConfig

        public ServiceConfig getServiceConfig(java.lang.String node,
                                      java.lang.String id)
        returns the service specified with the given id and the given node. If a service configuration is not found in the specified node, then it is searched in the defaults. If none is found there either, then a null is returned.
        Parameters:
        node - the nodeId scope on which to do the request or null
        id - the unique string identifying the service
